    Jayson Tatum established himself to become among the best players in the NBA since joining the league back in 2017. He was selected third overall in the 2016 draft, quickly becoming an important part in Boston's lineup, helping the Celtics reach the Eastern Conference Finals on multiple occasions and earning himself five All-Star selections through 2024. Scoring machine, defender, and leader of the second unit, Tatum averaged 26.9 points, 8.1 rebounds, and 4.9 assists during the 2023-24 season. He has since led the Celtics to an NBA championship in 2024 and placed himself among the ranks of the best players in the league.
